abstract: As the South Carolina primary unfolds Saturday, Bernie Sanders won’t be hustling for last-minute votes in Charleston or courting party elders in the state capital of Columbia. Rather, he'll be invading Elizabeth Warren’s home turf.
snippet: As the South Carolina primary unfolds Saturday, Bernie Sanders won’t be hustling for last-minute votes in Charleston or courting party elders in the state capital of Columbia. Rather, he'll be invading Elizabeth Warren’s home turf.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the South Carolina primary unfolds Saturday, Bernie Sanders won’t be hustling for last-minute votes in Charleston or courting party elders in the state capital of Columbia. Rather, he'll be invading Elizabeth Warren’s home turf.
headline_main: Sanders Makes Bold Play to Win Primary on Warren’s Home Turf
headline_print_headline: Sanders Makes Bold Play to Win Primary on Warren’s Home Turf

abstract: Senate Democrats on Tuesday blocked a pair of Republican bills that would ban most late-term abortions and threaten prison for doctors who don't try saving the life of infants born alive during abortions.
snippet: Senate Democrats on Tuesday blocked a pair of Republican bills that would ban most late-term abortions and threaten prison for doctors who don't try saving the life of infants born alive during abortions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Democrats on Tuesday blocked a pair of Republican bills that would ban most late-term abortions and threaten prison for doctors who don't try saving the life of infants born alive during abortions.
headline_main: Dems Thwart Senate Republicans on 2 Abortion-Related Bills
headline_print_headline: Dems Thwart Senate Republicans on 2 Abortion-Related Bills

abstract: “It was the woman of a year ago,” one Warren supporter said after her debate performance last week. “She’s showing us why we supported her in the beginning.”

abstract: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders has widened his lead for the Democratic presidential nomination and overtaken Joe Biden in support among African Americans - a voting bloc that until now has largely favored the former vice president, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday.
snippet: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders has widened his lead for the Democratic presidential nomination and overtaken Joe Biden in support among African Americans - a voting bloc that until now has largely favored the former vice president, according to a Reu...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders has widened his lead for the Democratic presidential nomination and overtaken Joe Biden in support among African Americans - a voting bloc that until now has largely favored the former vice president, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday.
headline_main: Sanders Surpasses Biden Among African American Voters: Reuters/Ipsos Poll
headline_print_headline: Sanders Surpasses Biden Among African American Voters: Reuters/Ipsos Poll

abstract: Bernie Sanders' surge to the front of the Democratic presidential contest has echoes of Donald Trump's improbable 2016 nomination, according to Republican strategists who tried and failed to stop the man who later won the presidency.
snippet: Bernie Sanders' surge to the front of the Democratic presidential contest has echoes of Donald Trump's improbable 2016 nomination, according to Republican strategists who tried and failed to stop the man who later won the presidency.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bernie Sanders' surge to the front of the Democratic presidential contest has echoes of Donald Trump's improbable 2016 nomination, according to Republican strategists who tried and failed to stop the man who later won the presidency.
headline_main: Republicans See Echoes of Trump's Improbable Rise in Sanders' Surge
headline_print_headline: Republicans See Echoes of Trump's Improbable Rise in Sanders' Surge

abstract: A new National Labor Relations Board rule scales back the responsibility of parent companies for violations by franchisees or contractors.
snippet: A new National Labor Relations Board rule scales back the responsibility of parent companies for violations by franchisees or contractors.
lead_paragraph: The National Labor Relations Board announced a new regulation on Tuesday that makes it harder to challenge companies over their labor practices, potentially affecting the rights of millions of workers.

abstract: Surging Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under withering fire in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, as rivals attacked the high cost of his ambitious economic agenda and warned he would cost the party the White House and control of Congress.

lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Surging Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under withering fire in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, as rivals attacked the high cost of his ambitious economic agenda and warned he would cost the party the White House and control of Congress.
headline_main: Rivals Question Front-Runner Sanders' Electability at Rowdy South Carolina Democratic Debate
